Description: M-Lab provides the largest collection of open Internet performance data on the planet.
Headquarters Regions: Dallas/Fort Worth Metroplex, Southern US
Full Description: When an Internet application doesn't work as expected, how can you tell whether the problem is caused by your connection, the application or something else? It can be very difficult for professional network administrators, let alone average Internet users, to answer this sort of question today. Transparency has always been an essential component of the Internet's success, and Internet users deserve to be well-informed about the performance of their broadband connections. For that to happen, researchers need resources to develop new analytical tools. That's where M-Lab comes in. M-Lab is an open, distributed server platform on which researchers can deploy open source Internet measurement tools. The data collected by those tools is released in the public domain. The goal of M-Lab is to advance network research and empower the public with useful information about their broadband and mobile connections. By enhancing Internet transparency, M-Lab helps sustain a healthy, innovative Internet.

Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: The Barrett Group is an executive career management firm that has served thousands of executive clients for 30 years. The firm differs from a recruitment firm because they work directly for the client/job candidate instead of working for an employer. Their hands-on approach is very comprehensive and the benefits they offer their clients are extensive, reaching beyond just getting the job. When a client first seeks out the Barrett Group, they do so because they are typically looking to either find a new career or change career paths. In the initial step (the Clarity Program©) the Barrett Group reviews the client’s needs and wants, explores who they really are and helps them clearly articulate their career goals. This process is often very enlightening for clients; many report that it helps them define their goals, find new motivation, focus, and drive. The Barret Group reviews each client’s Clarity Program© findings and then sets out to help the client discover the perfect position. When assisting the client for an upcoming interview, for example, the Barret Group has a team of expert negotiators that will prepare the clients for negotiating the best compensation plan for themselves. This team of experts is so phenomenally skilled in their field, that past clients have reported to have received offers that were tens of thousands of dollars higher than they would have been if it were not for the guidance they had received beforehand from the Barret Group’s negotiation team. After landing the role in their current or new career path, a client continues to receive career management support from the Barrett Group. When there are performance reviews, clients can rest assured that they will be more than prepared for them and come out the other side with a top dollar raise or promotion thanks to the continued guidance from the Barrett Group.
